 ## Login/logout part
 - Template : security/login.html.twig
 - Controller : Controller/SecurityController.php
 ```php
/**
     * @Route("/login", name="app_login")
     */
    public function login(AuthenticationUtils $authenticationUtils): Response
    {
        // get the login error if there is one
        $error = $authenticationUtils->getLastAuthenticationError();
        // last username entered by the user
        $lastUsername = $authenticationUtils->getLastUsername();

        return $this->render('security/login.html.twig', [
            'last_username' => $lastUsername, 
            'error' => $error,
        ]);
    }
 ```
The route is used to define the function that will process.
The render function call the template used for the view with parameters needed.
When the form is submitted, the class AppAdminAuthenticator in the controller Security/AppAdminAuthenticator.php is called.
About the role given, it is in the bin/config/packages/security.yaml :
```yaml
access_control:
        - { path: ^/admin, roles: ROLE_ADMIN }
```
-> this gives permission to all routes beginning by /admin to users with the role ROLE_ADMIN.

